Build step skipped.","type":"stdout","timestamp":"2026-02-23T23:18:23.078020Z","hidden":false,"batch":1,"order":11},{"command":"docker exec f8woo0k8gk44s4sgcwskcswk bash -c 'cat /artifacts/f8woo0k8gk44s4sgcwskcswk/Dockerfile'","output":"# Unified Dockerfile for VidAI - runs API and Worker together
FROM python:3.11-slim

ENV PYTHONDONTWRITEBYTECODE=1 \
    PYTHONUNBUFFERED=1 \
    PIP_NO_CACHE_DIR=1 \
    PIP_DISABLE_PIP_VERSION_CHECK=1 \
    PORT=8000

# Install system dependencies
RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
    ffmpeg \
    curl \
    fonts-dejavu-core \
    fonts-roboto \
    fontconfig \
    supervisor \
    && fc-cache -f \
    && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

WORKDIR /app

# Copy requirements and install
COPY requirements.txt .
RUN pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt

# Copy application
COPY app/ ./app/
COPY scripts/ ./scripts/
COPY assets/ ./assets/
COPY alembic/ ./alembic/
COPY alembic.ini .

RUN chmod +x ./scripts/run_migrations.sh && mkdir -p /data/jobs

# Simple start script instead of supervisor for faster startup
RUN echo '#!/bin/bash\n\
./scripts/run_migrations.sh\n\
echo "Starting API server..."\n\
uvicorn app.main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000 &\n\
API_PID=$!\n\
sleep 5\n\
echo "Starting Celery worker..."\n\
celery -A app.core.celery_app worker --loglevel=info --concurrency=1 &\n\
WORKER_PID=$!\n\
wait $API_PID $WORKER_PID' > /app/start.sh && chmod +x /app/start.sh

EXPOSE 8000

HEALTHCHECK --interval=60s --timeout=30s --start-period=60s --retries=5 \
    CMD curl -f http://localhost:8000/health || exit 1
